# Deploy folder – env reference
# Copy from repo root .env (or set in your host). Do not commit .env.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Medusa backend (deploy-site/medusa-backend)
# Use the same Supabase + Upstash credentials as in root .env
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Copy these from repo root .env into deploy-site/medusa-backend/.env
# (or set them in Railway/Render when deploying the backend)
#
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://...   # Supabase connection URI (Settings → Database)
# REDIS_URL=rediss://...         # Upstash Redis URL
#
# Also set in medusa-backend/.env (from medusa-backend/.env.template):
# STORE_CORS=...
# ADMIN_CORS=...
# AUTH_CORS=...
# JWT_SECRET=...
# COOKIE_SECRET=...
#
# Payment: backend is configured for PayPal only (no Stripe). Medusa v2 has no
# official PayPal provider yet; the built-in "system" provider (manual/COD) is
# used until you add a custom PayPal provider.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional: if you run scripts from deploy-site that need root .env
# Symlink or copy: cp ../../.env .env (then .env stays gitignored)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
